  "text": "Although many methods to construct matrix satisfying RIP(especially randomization method) have been brought forward [CITATION_1] , a lack of effective means for testing RIP and estimating RIP constant of a given deterministic matrix is still a hidden trouble for practitioners and user of compressed sensing technique [CITATION_2] , no exception for us. It is very hard to verify RIP of matrix used in STAP operation based on sparse recovery algorithm theoretically. So the detailed conditions for L 0 /L 1 equivalence will not be checked in our research. Fortunately, no severe consequence was encountered generally, because simply using L 1 optimization could we find the solution of (13) with some characteristic of sparsity (although it maybe isn't the most sparse one). That is just what we want in most cases.",
